transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about shipping package configuration master packages.
Create multiple master packages with different box sizes configurations and use them while creating product shipping packages.
Configure product wise shipping packages.
Enter details such as weight class, Max weight, length class, package length, width, height etcetera.
There are two ways to calculate package height, default and dynamic.
Dynamic height calculation will allow you to enter material thickness and calculate height in real time.
Shipment Package Calculator a section where you can troubleshoot and calculate the best fit box and the right number of box packages required for order shipment by yourself.
Let's see how you can configure it in admin.
Click on Store configuration and go to shipping method to configure master packages.
Click on Manage master package to add master package.
Click on add button.
Here you can configure master package like you can set master package name, weight, unit, single package weight, box weight and all package dimensions for standard as well as custom products.
Here you can see we have configured for master packages.
Let's see how we can use these master packages product wise.
For that click on shipping method.
Use third party shipping for example UPS action and go to shipping package configuration.
Here we are taking standard business card where we have already done setup.
Click on edit button.
Here you can see how we have assigned master packages along with master package we can add custom package for each product or for product size by click on add button.
Here you can see we have added one custom package.
For package height we have two options available default and dynamic.
The advantage of dynamic height is the package height will be calculated according to material thickness which will reduce package wastage.
As we select dynamic height we will be able to add material thickness and additional height.
Click on back button.
For all these configuration we have done how we can troubleshoot and calculate package boxes.
For that we have given one button named as package calculator.
Here you need to select product and need to put order weight and as you will click on calculate package it will show you best package combination with least wastage.
As we have added order weight of £45 and system is showing 2 packages of £25 and wastage will be 4.5 LB.
If you have any queries please contact us at support@onprintshop.com.
Thank you.
